# Project: UX Collab — Visual-First UI/UX Agent Skill

## What This Is

A reusable agent skill package for visual-first UI/UX collaboration. Contains one skill (`ux-collab`) plus Claude Code and GitHub Copilot plugin manifests.

## Structure

```
skills/
└── ux-collab/
    ├── SKILL.md                 # The skill (project-agnostic)
    ├── optimize-screenshot.sh   # Screenshot optimization helper
    └── docs/
        └── project-setup.md    # Per-project .ux-collab.md config guide
.claude-plugin/
└── plugin.json                  # Claude Code Marketplace manifest
.github/
├── copilot.json                 # GitHub Copilot agent definition
├── skill-index.json             # Discovery index
└── plugin/
    └── plugin.json              # Copilot plugin manifest
```

## Skills

| Skill | Trigger |
|-------|---------|
| `ux-collab` | "let's work on the UI", "show me what it looks like", "take a screenshot", "create a wireframe", "design the layout" |

## Key Design Decisions

- **Skill is project-agnostic** — all project-specific config (routes, brand tokens, file paths, open decisions) lives in a `.ux-collab.md` file at the consuming project's root
- **Lucid is optional** — skill has a full Markdown wireframe fallback for Step 3
- **Script uses relative path** — `./optimize-screenshot.sh` is always resolved relative to the SKILL.md location

## When Contributing

- Keep SKILL.md project-agnostic — no hardcoded routes, paths, or brand tokens
- Update `docs/project-setup.md` if the `.ux-collab.md` schema changes
- Bump `version` in both `package.json` and `SKILL.md` frontmatter metadata when making changes
